Before I start, I have to recommend you check out my friend @SaturnaliaSund1's own thread on the same subject, with different conspiracies discussed. I am sure you will all love to read it. Also follow him: @SaturnaliaSund1 #ff

1. God's Last Wish

According to this theory, which is related to Alexander Dugin's theology, the Russian people are chosen to be the nation that will bring the end of the world, which will end the story arc of humanity and bring the Apocalypse. This is God's final wish.

Another interpretation might be the idea of some Pre-Soviet theologians, who claimed that the act of Creation "shattered" God and it is our mission to "rebuild" Him, which is also the final goal of humanity. This idea is called "Godbuilding" but is mostly unknown in the West.

2. Nano-UFOs

This is related to a niche theory that Air Rods - mysterious objects appearing in many photos - who some claim are not photographic errors but real high-wavelength creatures, are actually miniature UFOs.

I will write a thread on them soon, quite fascinating stuff!

3. Meth Immortality

Meth has many interesting effects on the human body, like giving unnatural strength. Some believe that a form of it can be used to reinvigorate the body and even bring immortality - like the mythical Ambrosia. Allegedly the Nazis experimented with this.
sniffing salts

4. Trepanning

An incredibly ancient (Neolithic times) and VERY popular proto-surgical operation - drilling a hole in the skull to expose the Dura mater

Even though it seems crazy, some pseudo-scientist believe in it even today. It can allegedly be used to treat mental disorders

5. Sky snag theory

If I am not getting confused, this refers to the belief that the sky is an actual biological firmament above us. Parts of it that "die" fall down as meteorites and other space debris.
just put it there as a joke tbh never used irl

6. Trees are mammals

Trees are able to communicate with each other, using funguses in the ground as means of connection, in a similar manner to our Internet. They are able to report on danger, climate changes, and other stuff. This is scarcely researched but a DEEP rabbit hole.
ye the theory is a meme, still felt the need to put this one here tho

7. Solar Plexus Glider

A spiritual cryptid predator that attacks humans through their Solar Plexus chakra and spreads from human to human like an infection. Imagine the alien from the movie, but existing on the spiritual realm.

Most likely some kind of a demon.
The original is a meme, I wanted to just say something interesting for this one !

8. Tesseract Earth

The belief that Earth actually has the form of a cube. It does make sense from a symbolical standpoint, and can be related to a few theological theories.

9. Paleolithic Deep State

One theory suggests that a few generations after it appeared in humans, consciousness was somehow "lost" again, but a few men attained it through these years. They did not enlight their brothers, but started a secret society, which is still alive today.

10. MKULTRA (ongoing)

I mean, this should not come as a surprise. The highly satanic MKULTRA experiments are continuing to this day, and I myself can not imagine how twisted and horrifying they have gotten since the 70s.

Bonus: Research Elsagate

Like deep web markets, but in real life. You are able to purchase drugs, slaves, weapons, nuclear shit etc. Some like to add to the theory saying you can buy arcane magical stuff, sorcery, and even human souls.

13. Runescape in New York

I think this one is just a joke, but an explanation I've heard is parts of Runescape mirror some New York areas and somehow signify specific buildings, which are said to serve some insidious purpose, housing chambers of secret societies and experiments.

14. Empty Internet

A majority of Internet users are not real people, but very well-designed AI bots that are able to interact with people.

15. SCHNELLonline

Some very old 3D virtual world chatting game, with some very bizarre realms/places in it. It is rumored to have contained hidden occult messages and somehow was related to pedophile cabals.

16. Golf rumors

Joke aside, it refers to two things:

1. Many of the very expensive, high-class, low membership golfing clubs are actually a cover for a pedophilia ring. Under many golf courts there are facilities with child-slaves.

2. The name of a CIA "glass camera" project. This device could allegedly be used by Astral Projection travelers, hired by CIA, to take a photograph of what they were observing.

E.G. an astral agent is sent to see some highly secretive documents, he takes a pic, no one knows how.

And with it, we conclude this. I might make another thread soon with some theories I've missed on purpose, or with a few from a different iceberg. For now, this is all, and I seriously hope y'all enjoyed our journey.
